                        <div class="process-info">
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-4">
                                    <p class="font-jaapokki fs-6 text-black text-center">
                                        <span>THE FIRST THING TO DO IN</span> <br>
                                        <span>MAKING SOFTWARE IS THAT</span> <br>
                                        <span>WE UNDERSTAND THE NEED</span><br>
                                        <span>OF THE CUSTOMER.</span>
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-4">
                                    <p>We Understand his words carefully and make an accurate story. When all the information is gathered, we create a SRS document by following the user story and use case. From finalizing the UI of the software to the user
                                        experience, everything is discussed.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-4">
                                    <p>
                                        A team can't start working until they have the business logic in mind. Software development is nothing if not malleable. Requirements are not written in ink, they are written in pencil, so to speak.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
